text: Moesha is an American television sitcom. It aired on UPN from January 23, 1996, to May 14, 2001. It stars R&B; singer Brandy Norwood as Moesha Denise Mitchell, an African-American teenager living with her upper middle class family in the Leimert Park neighborhood of Los Angeles. It focused on the life of a black upper-middle-class family through the eyes of a typical girl named Moesha.
